The Part Catalogue Package show the design elements around a parts evalaution and potential selection. The package that makes up the Part Catalogue contains:
  1. Part Inputs Canvas - a summary of the part with critical design aspects
  2. Parts Specs Package - Containing the Key Part Specification that are of interest to the design
  3. Parts Evaluation Canvas - which shows the pluses, deltas, gaps, and challenges based upon the initial part evaluation.
The <<NewCataloguePart>> Parts Specifications contains the package of specifications of the part that are relevant to the design inputs and design specifications.

<font color="#ff4500">The Pain Point Brainstorm Canvas illustrates the different pains that the stakeholders are experiencing with respect to the problem and the problem statement. This diagram also shows the pluses or positive things that are being experienced now and the deltas or experiences that need to be eliminated or improved upon. </font> <font color="#ff4500"> </font><font color="#ff4500">The pain point brainstorm canvas was created to captured the current lay of the land with regard to the business process/product being analyzed. A pain point brainstorm was created for each of the stakeholders from their perspective. </font> <font color="#ff4500"> </font><font color="#ff4500">The pain point analysis also combine the common Plus - Delta analysis tool because the brainstorming workshops often generate discussion elements which identify what is going well and what needs to be changed. This tool asks participants to reflect on their continuous improvement and inform the changes needed to achieve higher performance. The Plus Delta inclusion involved drawing two additional areas in the analysis diagram, where one represents the positive feedback (what the group thinks went well) and the other represents the negative feedback (what the group thinks didn't go well and needs improvement).</font>
take away - things it is good for, things it is not good for
